<p><h3>About the instructor</h3> The course instructor is Alan
Agresti.  He is a visiting professor at Harvard University and a
Distinguished Professor Emeritus, Department of Statistics, University
of Florida.  He is the author of five books and more than 100 research
articles.  Agresti has presented short courses and given lectures
about categorical data methods for universities, industry, and
professional organizations in more than 30 countries.  He has received
an Honorary Doctor of Science from De Montfort University (UK), the
Statistician of the Year Award from the Chicago chapter of the
American Statistical Association, and the first Herman Callaert
Leadership Award in Biostatistical Education and Dissemination from
Hasselt University in
Belgium.  <a href="http://www.stat.ufl.edu/~aa">Agresti home page at
Univ. of Florida.</a> </h3>

